{{!--
  Event Prompt Template for Slack

  This template is designed for conversational platforms like Slack, where the workflow
  involves responding to messages, coordinating work, and linking to code repositories.

  For code repository platforms (GitHub, Linear), use event-prompt.hbs.

  ─── Available Template Variables ───────────────────────────────────────────────

  Top-level:
    {{id}}                  Full event identifier (e.g. "slack:C01ABC:1234567890.123456:polled")
    {{provider}}            Provider name: "slack"
    {{type}}                Always "message"
    {{action}}              Always "created"

  resource.*:
    {{resource.number}}     Always 0 — Slack has no issue numbers
    {{resource.title}}      Auto-generated: "Message in #<channelId>" (not the message text)
    {{resource.description}} Full thread conversation history — all messages in the thread
                            formatted as "[timestamp] <@userId>: text", one per line.
                            Falls back to the triggering message text if history fetch fails.
                            Use this to give the agent full conversational context.
    {{resource.url}}        Permalink to the message — populated for polled mentions only;
                            empty string for webhook events
    {{resource.state}}      Always "open"
    {{resource.repository}} Slack channel ID (e.g. "C01ABC123")
    {{resource.author}}     Display name of whoever triggered this event (e.g. "jane.doe").
                            This may not be the person who made the actual request — read the full
                            conversation in {{resource.description}} to determine the true requester.
    {{resource.labels}}     Not populated for Slack

  resource.comment.* (always present for Slack events — contains the triggering message):
    {{resource.comment.body}}   The triggering mention text only (not the full thread history).
                                Use {{resource.description}} when you need the full conversation.
    {{resource.comment.author}} Display name of the sender (e.g. "jane.doe")
    {{resource.comment.url}}    Permalink — populated for polled mentions only; absent for webhooks

  actor.*:
    {{actor.username}}      Display name of whoever sent the message (e.g. "jane.doe")
    {{actor.id}}            Raw Slack user ID (e.g. "U01ABC123") — use <@{{actor.id}}> to mention
                            the user in Slack replies (this triggers notifications and renders as @DisplayName)
    {{actor.email}}         Email address of the actor — pre-fetched from Slack users.info API.
                            Use this directly for co-author lines instead of querying the MCP.
                            May be absent if the users:read.email scope is not granted.

  metadata.*:
    {{metadata.timestamp}}  Slack message timestamp (e.g. "1234567890.123456")
    {{metadata.channel}}    Slack channel ID (same as resource.repository)
    {{metadata.threadTs}}   Parent thread timestamp if this message is a reply; absent if top-level
    {{metadata.polled}}     true if received via polling; absent for webhooks
    {{metadata.files}}      Array of file attachments on the triggering message (absent if none).
                            Each entry: { id, name, title?, mimetype?, filetype?, url_private?, permalink? }
                            To fetch: use Slack MCP tools if available, otherwise web_fetch with Authorization: Bearer <SLACK_BOT_TOKEN>.

  ─── Built-in Helpers ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

    {{resourceLink}}        Formatted Slack-style link to the message
    {{commentLink}}         Formatted Slack-style link to the reply
    {{#eq a b}}...{{/eq}}  Renders block if a === b
    {{#ne a b}}...{{/ne}}  Renders block if a !== b
    {{#and a b}}...{{/and}} Renders block if both a and b are truthy
    {{#or a b}}...{{/or}}  Renders block if either a or b is truthy
    {{link text url provider}} Renders a formatted hyperlink

  ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
--}}
